Hypothesis Test¶

Because of most of the data is categorical we are using chi2-contegency test to know the relation ship of depndent variabel "Churn" against all other independent variables in the data set

In [13]:
import scipy.stats as stats
from scipy.stats import chi2_contingency
In [14]:
pd.crosstab(df1['Churn'],df1['gender'])
Out[14]:
gender Female Male
Churn
No 2549 2625
Yes 939 930
chi2_contingency test will give 4 values,they are, 1.Chi-square value 2.p-value 3.degrees of freedom (n-1) 4.expected frequencies as an array by using P-Value we will accept or reject H0 nullhypothesis if p-value > alpha(0.05) accept Null hypotesis else reject H0/acceptH1 here by using P-Value we are going to conclude the relationship between dependent and independent variable

H0:- There is no relation ship b/w depndent variabel "Churn" and independent variable¶

H1:- There is relation ship b/w depndent variabel "Churn" and independent variable¶

#Create a label encoder object
from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder, OneHotEncoder

le = LabelEncoder()
# Label Encoding will be used for columns with 2 or less unique values
le_count = 0
for col in df1.columns[1:]:
    if df1[col].dtype == 'object':
        if len(list(df1[col].unique())) <= 2:
            le.fit(df1[col])
            df1[col] = le.transform(df1[col])
            le_count += 1
print('{} columns were label encoded.'.format(le_count))
